Travel slow if you can
If you have the luxury of time, try traveling by train or by boat to offset carbon emissions

resource.alt: People Traveling Set High-Res Vector Graphic

elements.content: Choose your airlines wisely

resource.alt: Man standing holding luggage during daytime

elements.content: Pick an airline that lets you offset your travel emissions when you purchase your ticket.

resource.alt: Vector Illustration Of Recycling Concept Flat Modern Design

elements.content: The amount of trash we generate personally on a daily and annual basis is staggering. Whenever possible, bring your own utensils and bags.

resource.alt: Paper Bag Full Of Grocery High-Res Vector Graphic

elements.content: Not only is it cheaper to buy in bulk, you reduce the amount of product packaging going into landfills.

resource.alt: Fast Food Flat Icons Set High-Res Vector Graphic
Person holding yellow and green gardening shovel

elements.content: Reducing food waste and composting are great ways to offset your footprint. Find a community compost station near you.
